### Variables
@baseUrl = http://localhost:3001

### 1. Obtener las preguntas (Endpoint existente)
GET {{baseUrl}}/questions
Accept: application/json

### --------------------------------------------------

### 2. Crear un País (Formulario 2)
POST {{baseUrl}}/countries
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "country_code": "MEX",
  "country_name": "Mexico",
  "details": {
    "language": "Spanish",
    "population": "128.9 million",
    "governmentType": "Federal Republic",
    "currency": "Mexican Peso",
    "typicalFood": "Tacos, Mole, Tamales",
    "climate": "Varies from tropical to desert"
  }
}

### --------------------------------------------------

### 3. Crear otro País (Para tener variedad)
POST {{baseUrl}}/countries
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "country_code": "JPN",
  "country_name": "Japan",
  "details": {
    "language": "Japanese",
    "currency": "Yen",
    "typicalFood": "Sushi, Ramen",
    "transport": "Shinkansen (Bullet Train)"
  }
}

### --------------------------------------------------

### 4. Crear una Entrevista con Respuestas (Formulario 1)
# Asegúrate de enviar un country_id que ya exista en la BD (como MEX o JPN)
# y topic_tag_ids que existan en tu tabla topic_tag-A
POST {{baseUrl}}/interviews
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "interviewer_name": "Alice Developer",
  "interviewee_name": "Juan Pérez",
  "country_id": "MEX",
  "responses": [
    {
      "topic_tag_id": 1,
      "question": "What surprised you the most about the culture?",
      "answer": "The warmth and hospitality of the people everywhere I went."
    },
    {
      "topic_tag_id": 2,
      "question": "What was your favorite local dish?",
      "answer": "Definitely the authentic street tacos al pastor."
    },
    {
      "topic_tag_id": 1,
      "question": "Any common phrases you learned?",
      "answer": ""
    }
  ]
}

### --------------------------------------------------

### 5. Insertar todas las categorías (Topics)
POST {{baseUrl}}/topics
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "topics": [
    "Background & Location",
    "Core Cultural Values & Beliefs",
    "Daily Life & Society",
    "Greetings, Manners & Social Etiquette",
    "Food & Traditions",
    "Practical Travel Considerations",
    "Language & Slang",
    "Cultural Adjustment Experience (BYUI / Mission Context)",
    "Reflection & Advice",
    "Follow-Up"
  ]
}

### --------------------------------------------------

### 6. Obtener un País específico (Para verificar que se creó correctamente)
GET http://localhost:3001/countries/JPN
Accept: application/json